<p>I know that a copy constructor is always created by default even if I don't explicitly create one. Is the same true for a move constructor? Let's assume a have a very simple class:</p>  <pre><code>class SimpleClass {  public:     SimpleClass(int value) :             member(value)     {}      int member;  }; </code></pre>  <p>Do I explicitly need to write <code>SimpleClass(SimpleClass &amp;&amp;other) default</code> to create the default move constructor or not?</p>